Its like we did:
\[x\] \[y = f_1(x)\] \[g = f_2(y)\] \[h = f_3(g)\]

.

## [1] 36

## [1] 36

c(1:10, NA) %>% mean(na.rm = T) %>% round() %>% .^2
## [1] 36

2.2 additional operators:

%$%

Some functions, e.g lm() , have a data argument, which allows the direct use of names inside the data as part of the call. Other functions like cor() or var() dont.
This operator exposes the contents of the left-hand side object to the expression on the right to give a similar benefit, see the examples.

example:
cor() is a function that accepts vectors in its input

cor(mtcars$mpg, mtcars$wt)
## [1] -0.8676594

mtcars %>% cor(mpg, wt)
## Error in pmatch(use, c("all.obs", "complete.obs", "pairwise.complete.obs", : object 'wt' not found

# This should do it: 
mtcars %$% cor(mpg, wt)
## [1] -0.8676594
%<>% assignment

%<>% assignment <-.
:

df <- mtcars

df <- df %>% mutate(new_var = gear * carb)

# and also to
df <- mutate(df,new_var = gear * carb )

:

df %<>% mutate(new_var = gear * carb)

3.2 filter

filter rows with filter.

Use , or & is the same.

filter(f1, month == 1, day == 1)
## # A tibble: 842 x 6
##    year month   day dep_time sched_dep_time dep_delay
##   <int> <int> <int>    <int>          <int>     <dbl>
## 1  2013     1     1      517            515         2
## 2  2013     1     1      533            529         4
## 3  2013     1     1      542            540         2
## 4  2013     1     1      544            545        -1
## 5  2013     1     1      554            600        -6
## # ... with 837 more rows

Its the same as:

filter(flights, month == 1 & day == 1)

or is |

filter(flights, month == 1 | month == 2)

-%in%:

filter(flights, month %in% c(1,2))
filter(flights, month %in% 1:3)

de-morgan.

!(x & y) is the same as !x | !y, and !(x | y) is the same as !x & !y.

Two equivalents:

filter(flights, !(arr_delay > 120 | dep_delay > 120)) 

# same as
filter(flights, arr_delay <= 120, dep_delay <= 120)

baseR :

flights[flights$arr_delay <= 120 & flights$dep_delay <= 120, ]

dplyr -$. -environment. data masking.
baseR . .

head(flights$arr_delay <= 120 & flights$dep_delay <= 120)
